  "text": "The gene deletion library used in this study was constructed based on the principle of homologous recombination, as previously reported [CITATION_1] . In brief, for each strain the open reading frame was replaced and tagged by homologous recombination with a deletion cassette consisting of the KanMX module (the selectable resistance gene KanMX4 and a pair of unique 20-mer molecular bar-codes (up-tag and down-tag) on both sides flanking the KanMX4 gene) and its flanking homologous regions to the chromosome (RHG).",
  "correct_citation": {
